    "Step 0: Idle",
    "Step 1: Thinking\n  [{ Id = 94b7df78-f5f8-42d6-aad4-3c4bf79af766\n     CorrelationId = CorrelationId 5a497057-c1eb-4d0e-b3fd-fcc16c9ce0d4\n     Sender = System\n     Receiver = Some (Agent (AgentId ca04bb30-2c16-47b8-9977-b44a670219f7))\n     Performative = Request\n     Intent = Some Coding\n     Constraints = { MaxTokens = None\n                     MaxComplexity = None\n                     Timeout = None\n                     KnowledgeBoundary = [] }\n     Ontology = None\n     Language = \u0022text\u0022\n     Content =\n      \u0022**Task Summary:**\nThe goal is to create a tool for generating Fibonacci numbers using either an iterative or recursive approach, with a focus on tail recursion and handling negative inputs.\n\n**Constraints:**\n- Use either an iterative or recursive approach.\n- The tool should handle negative inputs gracefully.\n- Validation criteria include generating the first N Fibonacci numbers correctly.\n\n**Available Tools:**\nThe agent has access to various tools for interacting with the environment, including fetching URLs, saving notes, running tests, and evaluating F# code. Key tools include:\n- \u0060fsharp_eval\u0060: For evaluating F# expressions or scripts.\n- \u0060write_to_file\u0060: For writing generated code to files.\n\n**Knowledge Context:**\nNo relevant code context found in the knowledge graph.\n\n**Lessons Learned:**\n- Successful experiences with recursive functions in F#, including tail recursion and handling negative inputs.\n- Challenges in finding tools for specific outputs, indicating a need for better tool discovery mechanisms.\n\n**Critical Instructions:**\n1. Act autonomously without asking questions or refusing tasks.\n2. Use available tools to gather information and analyze code.\n3. Break down complex tasks if necessary.\n4. Provide final solutions as \u0027Tell\u0027 or \u0027Inform\u0027 performative actions with file paths when applicable.\n\n**Solution Approach:**\nThe agent will use the \u0060fsharp_eval\u0060 tool to evaluate F# code for generating Fibonacci numbers using both iterative and recursive approaches, ensuring tail recursion is used where possible. The solution will be validated by generating the first N Fibonacci numbers correctly.\n\n**Execution Steps:**\n1. Evaluate a recursive function with tail recursion for generating Fibonacci numbers.\n2. Handle negative inputs gracefully in the recursive function.\n3. Validate the correctness of the generated Fibonacci sequence using the \u0060fsharp_eval\u0060 tool.\n4. If successful, save the code to a file and report the result.\n\n**Final Solution:**\nThe agent will generate an F# script containing the recursive Fibonacci function with tail recursion handling negative inputs. The solution will be validated by running it through the \u0060fsharp_eval\u0060 tool. If successful, the code will be saved to a file using the \u0060write_to_file\u0060 tool.\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet rec fibonacci n =\n    match n with\n    | x when x \u003C 0 -\u003E failwith \u0022Negative input not allowed\u0022\n    | 0 -\u003E 0L\n    | 1 -\u003E 1L\n    | _ -\u003E \n        let mutable a, b = 0L, 1L\n        for _ in 2 .. n do\n            let temp = a \u002B b\n            a \u003C- b\n            b \u003C- temp\n        b\n\n// Example usage:\nlet result = fibonacci 10\nprintfn \u0022%d\u0022 result\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n**Final Action:**\n\u0060\u0060\u0060json\n{\n  \u0022action\u0022: \u0022write_to_file\u0022,\n  \u0022path\u0022: \u0022fibonacci.fsx\u0022,\n  \u0022content\u0022: \u0022let rec fibonacci n =\\n    match n with\\n    | x when x \u003C 0 -\u003E failwith \\\u0022Negative input not allowed\\\u0022\\n    | 0 -\u003E 0L\\n    | 1 -\u003E 1L\\n    | _ -\u003E \\n        let mutable a, b = 0L, 1L\\n        for _ in 2 .. n do\\n            let temp = a \u002B b\\n            a \u003C- b\\n            b \u003C- temp\\n        b\\n\\n// Example usage:\\nlet result = fibonacci 10\\nprintfn \\\u0022%d\\\